<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/981236-can-anyone-else-make-up-their-mind-about">Can anyone else make up their mind about Carver? This story is told in such dry fashion and is obviously a biographical parallel that I have trouble giving him points for creativity. I like his visceral writing and detailed analysis of setting but his tone is so subdued and detached, aspects he&#39;s mastered. At times I feel as though he&#39;s insincere. Does anyone else feel conflicted about him?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_981236'><a id="like_count_community_question_981236" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/981236?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">3 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F11446.Will_You_Please_Be_Quiet_Please_">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
